gaffer.data.elementdefinition.schema

Class DataElementDefinitionValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • gaffer.data.elementdefinition.TypedElementDefinitionValidator<DataElementDefinition>
      • gaffer.data.elementdefinition.schema.DataElementDefinitionValidator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Validator<DataElementDefinition>

    public class DataElementDefinitionValidator
extends TypedElementDefinitionValidator<DataElementDefinition>
    An DataElementDefinitionValidator extends TypedElementDefinitionValidator and adds additional validation for a DataElementDefinition. To be able to aggregate 2 similar elements together ALL properties have to be aggregated together. So this validator checks that either no properties have aggregator functions or all properties have aggregator functions defined.

      boolean validate(DataElementDefinition elementDef)
      Carries out the validation as per TypedElementDefinitionValidator and then checks all FilterFunctions and AggregateFunctions defined are compatible with the identifiers and properties - this is done by comparing the function input and output types with the identifier and property types.
